ry Blake于大约1385年出生在英国維爾爾卡爾內时，他的父亲William Blake26岁，母亲Elizabeth Power21岁。他于1410年与Margaret Bellett结婚。他们至少是2个儿子的父母。他去世于1467年10月29日在他的家乡享年83岁。"},"hr":{"about 1385–29 October 1467":"oko 1385.–29. listopada 1467.","1382–1439":"1382–1439","1385–1467":"1385–1467","1390–1474":"1390–1474","1385–1473":"1385–1473","1412–1474":"1412.–1474","1435–1471":"1435.–1471","1360–1461":"1360–1461","1365–1464":"1365–1464.","29 October 1467":"29. listopada 1467.","1473":"1473","1385":"1385","1461":"1461","1471":"1471","1360":"1360","1382":"1382","1380":"1380.","1390":"1390","1435":"1435.","1412":"1412.","1467":"1467","1455":"1455","1410":"1410.","1464":"1464.","1365":"1365","1474":"1474","about 1385":"oko 1385.","1439":"1439","1 December 1461":"1. prosinca 1461.","Andover, Hampshire, England":"Andover, Hampshire, England","Calne, Wiltshire, England":"Calne, Wiltshire, Engleska, United Kingdom","Calne, Calne and Quemberford, Wiltshire, England":"Calne, Wiltshire, England"},"cs":{"about 1385–29 October 1467":"okolo 1385–29. října 1467","1382–1439":"1382–1439","1385–1467":"1385–1467","1390–1474":"1390–1474","1385–1473":"1385–1473","1412–1474":"1412–1474","1435–1471":"1435–1471","1360–1461":"1360–1461","1365–1464":"1365–1464","29 October 1467":"29. října 1467","1473":"1473","1385":"1385","1461":"1461","1471":"1471","1360":"1360","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","1390":"1390","1435":"1435","1412":"1412","1467":"1467","1455":"1455","1410":"1410","1464":"1464","1365":"1365","1474":"1474","about 1385":"okolo 1385","1439":"1439","1 December 1461":"1. prosince 1461","Andover, Hampshire, England":"Andover, Hampshire, Anglie","Calne, Wiltshire, England":"Calne, Wiltshire, Anglie, United Kingdom","Calne, Calne and Quemberford, Wiltshire, England":"Calne, Wiltshire, Anglie"},"da":{"about 1385–29 October 1467":"omkring 1385–29. oktober 1467","1382–1439":"1382–1439","1385–1467":"1385–1467","1390–1474":"1390–1474","1385–1473":"1385–1473","1412–1474":"1412–1474","1435–1471":"1435–1471","1360–1461":"1360–1461","1365–1464":"1365–1464","29 October 1467":"29. oktober 1467","1473":"1473","1385":"1385","1461":"1461","1471":"1471","1360":"1360","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","1390":"1390","1435":"1435","1412":"1412","1467":"1467","1455":"1455","1410":"1410","1464":"1464","1365":"1365","1474":"1474","about 1385":"omkring 1385","1439":"1439","1 December 1461":"1. december 1461","Andover, Hampshire, England":"Andover, Hampshire, England","Calne, Wiltshire, England":"Calne, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","Calne, Calne and Quemberford, Wiltshire, England":"Calne, Wiltshire, England"},"nl":{"about 1385–29 October 1467":"circa 1385–29 oktober 1467","1382–1439":"1382–1439","1385–1467":"1385–1467","1390–1474":"1390–1474","1385–1473":"1385–1473","1412–1474":"1412–1474","1435–1471":"1435–1471","1360–1461":"1360–1461","1365–1464":"1365–1464","29 October 1467":"29 oktober 1467","1473":"1473","1385":"1385","1461":"1461","1471":"1471","1360":"1360","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","1390":"1390","1435":"1435","1412":"1412","1467":"1467","1455":"1455","1410":"1410","1464":"1464","1365":"1365","1474":"1474","about 1385":"circa 1385","1439":"1439","1 December 1461":"1 december 1461","Andover, Hampshire, England":"Andover, Hampshire, England","Calne, Wiltshire, England":"Calne, Wiltshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Calne, Calne and Quemberford, Wiltshire, England":"Calne, Wiltshire, England"},"en":{"about 1385–29 October 1467":"about 1385–29 October 1467","1382–1439":"1382–1439","1385–1467":"1385–1467","1390–1474":"1390–1474","1385–1473":"1385–1473","1412–1474":"1412–1474","1435–1471":"1435–1471","1360–1461":"1360–1461","1365–1464":"1365–1464","29 October 1467":"29 October 1467","1473":"1473","1385":"1385","1461":"1461","1471":"1471","1360":"1360","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","1390":"1390","1435":"1435","1412":"1412","1467":"1467","1455":"1455","1410":"1410","1464":"1464","1365":"1365","1474":"1474","about 1385":"about 1385","1439":"1439","1 December 1461":"1 December 1461","Andover, Hampshire, England":"Andover, Hampshire, England","Calne, Wiltshire, England":"Calne, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","Calne, Calne and Quemberford, Wiltshire, England":"Calne, Wiltshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Blake","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Scottish (England and central Scotland): variant of   Black   1, meaning ‘swarthy’ or ‘dark-haired’, from a byform of the Old English adjective <i>blæc</i>, <i>blac</i> ‘black’, with change of vowel length.","English: nickname from Middle English <i>blak(e)</i> (Old English <i>blāc</i>) ‘wan, pale, white, fair’. In Middle English the two words <i>blac</i> and <i>blāc</i>, with opposite meanings, fell together as Middle English <i>blake</i>. In the absence of independent evidence as to whether the person referred to was dark or fair, it is now impossible to tell which sense was originally meant.","English (Norfolk): nickname from Middle English <i>bleik</i>, <i>blaik</i>&gt;, <i>blek(e)</i> (Old Norse <i>bleikr</i>) ‘pale or sallow’ (in complexion)."],"variants":[{"name":"Bleak","meanings":["English: mostly a variant of   Blake  , but perhaps also of   Blick  . This form of the surname is now rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Black","meanings":["English and Scottish: chiefly from Middle English <i>blak(e)</i> ‘black’ (Old English <i>blæc</i>, <i>blaca</i>), a nickname given from the earliest times to a swarthy or dark-haired man. However, Middle English <i>blac</i> also meant ‘pale, wan’, a reflex of Old English <i>blāc</i> ‘pale, white’ with a shortened vowel. Compare   Blatch   and   Blick  . With rare exceptions it is impossible to disambiguate these antithetical senses in Middle English surnames. The same difficulty arises with   Blake   and   Block  .","Scottish: in Gaelic-speaking areas this name was adopted as a translation of the epithet <i>dubh</i> ‘dark, black-(haired)’, or of various other names based on Gaelic <i>dubh</i> ‘black’, see   Duff  .","Americanized form (translation into English) of various European surnames directly or indirectly derived from the adjective meaning ‘black, dark’, for example German and Jewish   Schwarz   and Slavic surnames beginning with <i>Čern-</i>, <i>Chern-</i> (see   Chern   and   Cherne  ), <i>Chorn-</i>, <i>Crn-</i> or <i>Czern-</i>."]},{"name":"Blaikie","meanings":["Scottish: nickname from a pet form of   Blake  ."]},{"name":"Blakes","meanings":["English: variant of   Blake  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]}]},{"name":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":70,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Henry Blake was born about 1385, in Calne, Wiltshire, England, his father, William Blake, was 26 and his mother, Elizabeth Power, was 21. He married Margaret Bellett in 1410. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died on 29 October 1467, in his hometown, at the age of 83."},"et":